 :tx/rationale "DOG-FOOD OBSERVATION: Build lock contention during parallel agent work. When a background agent is compiling (e.g., T2-3 adding serde derives triggers full recompile), ALL braid CLI commands block on 'waiting for file lock on build directory'. This makes the system unusable for 1-3 minutes. The AGENT_LAUNCH_PROTOCOL (INV-TOPOLOGY-003) says agents don't build, but when agents EDIT code, the next CLI invocation triggers a recompile and holds the lock. Possible fixes: (1) CARGO_TARGET_DIR per agent (already noted in Rule 3 of the protocol). (2) Separate build profiles for CLI vs background work. (3) The daemon (T2-5) would eliminate this entirely — the daemon holds pre-compiled state and doesn't need to recompile."
